    <section name="Requirements">
     <span class='shortdesc'>What do you need to run Hippo CMS?</span>

     <span class='add'>A table to show an overview of the requirements and support stacks. For support stacks see <a href='http://www.alfresco.com/services/support/stacks/2.2/'/></span>
     <span class='review'>Check agains http://www.hippocms.org/display/CMS/01.2+Hardware+Requirements</span>
     <span class='review'>Check if all statements true.</span>

      <subsection name="Operating System">
      
      <blockquote>  
        <table>
         <tr>
          <td>Overall</td>
   <td>
     <em><img src='../images/overall.png' alt='overall icon'/></em> 
   </td>
          <td>
              The Hippo ECM software runs on all modern operating systems
              that run <a href='http://www.sun.com/'>Sun</a>'s 
              <span class='expires'>Java 6 (or 5)</span> 
              correctly and put no severe limitations on allowed filenames and system calls.
	  </td>
         </tr>


         <tr>
          <td>
           Tested
          </td>
   <td>
     <em><img src='../images/tested.png' alt='Tested icon'/></em> 
   </td>
          <td>Hippo continuously tests the ECM on 
              <span class='expires'>
  <a href='http://www.microsoft.com/windows/windows-xp/default.aspx'>Microsoft Windows XP</a>
   and Linux: 
  <a href='http://www.ubuntu.com/'>Ubuntu</a>, 
  <a href='http://www.slackware.com/'>Slackware</a> and 
  <a href='http://www.debian.org'>Debian</a>.
  </span> 
              The Hippo ECM is also tested on other systems.  
          </td>
	 </tr>


         <tr>
          <td>Support
          </td>
   <td>
     <em><img src='../images/support.png' alt='support icon'/></em> 
   </td>

          <td>Hippo <span class='expires'>will support the new ECM</span> on all 
              modern <a href='http://www.microsoft.com'>Microsoft</a> Windows 
              and 
              <a href='http://www.linux.org/'>Linux</a> 
              systems:
              <a href='http://www.microsoft.com'>Microsoft</a> Windows: 
              <a href='http://www.microsoft.com/windows/windows-xp/default.aspx'>XP</a>, 
              <a href='http://www.microsoft.com/windows/windows-vista/default.aspx'>Vista</a>, 
              <a href='http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/windowsserver/2000/default.aspx'>2000</a>, 
              <a href='http://www.microsoft.com/windowsserver2003/default.mspx'>Server 2003</a>, etc...
              <a href='http://www.linux.org/'>Linux</a>: 
              <a href='http://www.ubuntu.com/'>Ubuntu</a>, 
              <a href='http://www.debian.org'>Debian</a>, 
              <a href='http://www.slackware.com/'>Slackware</a>, 
              <a href='http://www.redhat.com/'>Redhat</a>, 
              <a href='http://www.novell.com/linux/'>Suse</a>, etc... 
              Support for other
              systems is also possible.
          </td>
	 </tr>
	</table>
      </blockquote>
          <!--
          <ul>
          <li>Windows XP/2000, Windows Server 2003</li>
          <li>Linux: RedHat (RHEL), SUSE (SLES), Ubuntu, Debian, Slackware and other distributions</li>
