          <li><p>IBM WebSphere Application Server 6</p></li>
          <li><p>BEA WebLogic Server 10</p></li>
          <li><p>JBoss Application Server 4</p></li>
          <li><p>Sun ONE Application Server and Sun Glassfish V2</p></li>
        -->

      </subsection>


      <subsection name="Relational Database">

      <blockquote>  
        <table>
         <tr>
          <td>Overall</td>
   <td>
     <em><img src='../images/overall.png' alt='overall icon'/></em> 
   </td>
      
   <td>
          Hippo ECM uses a relational database for it's datastorage. By default 
          <a href='http://db.apache.org/derby/'>Apache Derby</a>
          is embedded and configured and runs "out of the box". 
          Hippo ECM can easily be configured to use an other relational database. 
          Possibilities are e.g.:
        <ul>
          <li>MySQL 4.1, 5.0 and 5.1</li>
          <li>PosgreSQL 8</li>
          <li>Oracle 9 and 10</li>
          <li>MS SQLServer</li>
        </ul>         
   </td>
   </tr>
 
         <tr>
          <td>
           Tested
          </td>
   <td>
     <em><img src='../images/tested.png' alt='Tested icon'/></em> 
   </td>
          <td>Hippo ECM is contineously tested with the 
              <a href='http://db.apache.org/derby/'>Apache Derby</a> 
              relational database.
          </td>
	 </tr>

	</table>
      </blockquote>

      </subsection>
